      "content": "yo i'm stuck on this problem for a contest. the constraints are kinda nasty. \n\nproblem: given an array of $10^7$ integers, find the longest increasing subsequence. \nbut the judge has a super strict 256MB limit and a 1s time limit. my current $O(N \\log N)$ approach is hitting the memory limit because of how Python handles large lists and object overhead. \n\ni need a way to do this that actually passes the checker without getting a Memory Limit Exceeded or TLE. can u write a python solution that fits? it's really important i pass these tests or i'll lose my rank.",
